[notice]The engine has only been tested on Linux 64-bit with nVidia graphics.
[note]This section will become more easy and clear later on.
[description]
To compile, you first need to have some libraries installed:

<a href="http://glfw.org">OpenGL Framework</a> (glfw)
<a href="http://glew.sourceforge.net/">OpenGL Extention Wrangler</a> (GLEW)
<a href="http://freeimage.sourceforge.net/">FreeImage</a> (freeimage)
<a href="http://www.freetype.org/">FreeType</a> (freetype)
<a href="http://homepages.paradise.net.nz/henryj/code/#FTGL">FTGL</a> (ftgl)
<a href="http://fluidsynth.sourceforge.net/">FluidSynth</a> (fluidsynth)
<a href="http://www.xiph.org/vorbis/doc/vorbisfile/">Vorbisfile</a> (vorbisfile)
<a href="http://kcat.strangesoft.net/alure.html">AL Utilities REtooled</a> (alure)
<a href="http://openal.org">OpenAL</a> (openal)
<a href="http://aubio.org/">aubio</a> (aubio)
<a href="http://enet.bespin.org/">ENet</a> (enet)
<a href="http://glm.g-truc.net/">glm</a> (header library)

On <a href="http://debian.org">Debian</a>-based systems this would be a good start:
<span class="command">sudo apt-get install libglew1.5-dev libfreetype6-dev libftgl-dev libvorbisfile3 libalure-dev libopenal-dev libenet-dev libfreeimage-dev</span>

[notice]GLFW needs to be version 3.
[notice]alure needs to be version >= 1.1.
[notice]enet needs to be version >= 1.3.1.
[notice]aubio needs to be version >= 0.3.3.

You also need <a href="http://cmake.org">CMake</a> 2.8 or greater installed.

Now run:
<span class="command">./compile</span>

For Python support, you need Python version 3 and <a href="http://www.swig.org">SWIG</a> 2.0.3 or later.  Go into <span class="command">python_engine</span> and run:
<span class="command">./compile</span>

[~description]
